The paper focuses on facial manipulation detection using deep learning techniques, specifically Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for detection, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of potential misuse of facial manipulation, which relates to cybersecurity and privacy, falling under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper proposes a novel strategy for removing GAN fingerprints, which involves optimization and algorithmic design, falling under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of state-of-the-art detection systems, which involves statistical analysis and experimental design, falling under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
